   networks to numerous potential vulnerabilities. Several studies have
   shown that anomaly-based Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS) achieves
   improved performance to identify unknown or zero-day attacks. In this
   paper, we propose a hybrid model for anomaly-based intrusion detection
   in SCADA networks using machine learning approach. In the first part, we
   present a robust hybrid model for anomaly-based intrusion detection in
   SCADA networks. Finally, we present a feature selection model for
   anomaly-based intrusion detection in SCADA networks by removing
   redundant and irrelevant features. Irrelevant features in the dataset
   can affect modeling power and reduce predictive accuracy. These models
