Abstract = {{Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition (SCADA) systems face the
   absence of a protection technique that can beat different types of
   intrusions and protect the data from disclosure while handling this data
   using other applications, specifically Intrusion Detection System (IDS).
   The SCADA system can manage the critical infrastructure of industrial
   control environments. Protecting sensitive information is a difficult
   task to achieve in reality with the connection of physical and digital
   systems. Hence, privacy preservation techniques have become effective in
   order to protect sensitive/private information and to detect malicious
   activities, but they are not accurate in terms of error detection,
   sensitivity percentage of data disclosure. In this paper, we propose a
   new Privacy Preservation Intrusion Detection (PPID) technique based on
   the correlation coefficient and Expectation Maximisation (EM) clustering
   mechanisms for selecting important portions of data and recognizing
   intrusive events. This technique is evaluated on the power system
