   constraints. In order to inject an exogenous control input without being
   detected the attacker will hijack the sensors, observe and record their
   readings for a certain amount of time and repeat them afterwards while
   carrying out his attack. The conditions under which the attacker can
   induce perturbation in the control loop without being detected is
