   an approach is proposed for the secure state estimation in
   cyber-physical systems with switching attacks. The attack signal causes
   a switch in the system behaviour. We consider only two system modes,
   nominal mode and attacked mode. As the switching sequence is unknown,
   information coming from IT cybersecurity layer is used to guide the
   switching signal of the observer mode. The residual signal provided by
