Organization = {{Idaho Natl Labs; Inst Elect \& Elect Engineers; IEEE Ind Elect Soc}},
Abstract = {{Attacks on critical infrastructures' Supervisory Control and Data
   Acquisition (SCADA) systems are beginning to increase. They are often
   initiated by highly skilled attackers, who are capable of deploying
   sophisticated attacks to exfiltrate data or even to cause physical
   damage. In this paper, we rehearse the rationale for protecting against
   cyber attacks and evaluate a set of Anomaly Detection (AD) techniques in
   detecting attacks by analysing traffic captured in a SCADA network. For
   this purpose, we have implemented a tool chain with a reference
   implementation of various state-of-the-art AD techniques to detect
