Abstract = {{This paper describes a novel domain-aware anomaly detection system that
   detects irregular changes in Modbus/TCP SCADA control register values.
   The research discovered the presence of three classes of registers: (i)
   sensor registers; (ii) counter registers; and (iii) constant registers.
   An automatic classifier was developed to identify these classes.
   Additionally, parameterized behavior models were created for each class.
   During its learning phase, the anomaly detection system used the
   classifier to identify the different types of registers and instantiated
   the model for each register based on its type. During the enforcement
   phase, the system detected deviations from the model. The anomaly
   detection system was evaluated using 131 h of traffic from a production
   SCADA system. The classifier had a true positive classification rate of
